
[1]abandonment

   ABAN'DONMENT, n.

   1. A total desertion; a state of being forsaken.

   2. In commerce, the relinquishing to underwriters all the property
   saved from loss by shipwreck, capture or other peril stated in the
   policy. This abandonment must be made before the insured can demand
   indemnification for a total loss.
